---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout title="Privacy & Data Stewardship | Junction Retro">
  <main class="py-24 px-8 md:px-16 selection:bg-slate-200">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto">
      
      <a href="/" class="text-[10px] uppercase tracking-[0.3em] text-slate-400 hover:text-slate-900 transition-colors mb-16 inline-block">
        ← Back to Home
      </a>

      <header class="mb-20 border-b border-slate-200 pb-12">
        <h1 class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-serif text-slate-900 mb-6 tracking-tighter italic">
          Privacy & <br />Data Stewardship
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.5em] text-slate-500 font-bold">
          Effective Date: March 30, 2026
        </p>
      </header>

      <article class="prose prose-slate prose-lg font-sans text-slate-700 leading-relaxed">
        
        <p class="italic text-xl text-slate-800 mb-12 font-serif">
          At Junction Retro, we believe that managing automotive history requires the same level of integrity as protecting your personal information.
        </p>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-slate-900 mb-4 uppercase tracking-tight">1. Data Controller</h2>
          <p>
            The entity responsible for your personal data is <strong>Junction Retro</strong>. For any questions regarding your digital dossier, please contact our archivists at <a href="mailto:contact@junction-retro.com" class="text-slate-900 underline decoration-slate-300 underline-offset-4 hover:decoration-slate-900 transition-all">Contact</a>.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-slate-900 mb-4 uppercase tracking-tight">2. Scope of Collection</h2>
          <p>We collect information necessary to provide a bespoke experience for the modern collector. This data includes:</p>
          <ul class="list-none space-y-4 pl-0">
            <li class="border-l-2 border-slate-200 pl-6"><strong class="text-slate-900">Identity Data:</strong> Full name, title, and professional affiliation.</li>
            <li class="border-l-2 border-slate-200 pl-6"><strong class="text-slate-900">Contact Data:</strong> Email address, telephone number, and physical billing/shipping address.</li>
            <li class="border-l-2 border-slate-200 pl-6"><strong class="text-slate-900">Technical Data:</strong> IP address, browser type, and location data captured during your session.</li>
          </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-slate-900 mb-4 uppercase tracking-tight">3. Legal Basis & Purpose</h2>
          <p>
            Processing is conducted under the <strong>General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR)</strong>. We utilize your information to facilitate vehicle acquisitions, refine our archival offerings, and satisfy Belgium financial regulations.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-slate-900 mb-4 uppercase tracking-tight">4. Retention & Security</h2>
          <p>
            Your records are treated as sensitive assets. Transactional data is retained for <strong>10 years</strong> to meet statutory requirements, while technical logs are purged after 180 days. All data is encrypted via TLS 1.3.
          </p>
        </section>

        <section class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl text-slate-900 mb-4 uppercase tracking-tight">5. Your Statutory Rights</h2>
          <p>
            As a data subject, you hold the right to access, rectify, or request the permanent erasure of your personal dossier. To invoke these rights, please submit a formal request to our Belgium headquarters.
          </p>
        </section>

      </article>

    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>

<style>
  strong {
    font-weight: 600;
    color: #0f172a;
  }
</style>